{"id": 4168, "title": "Ticket #4168: Have HTCondor force proxies to be 1024 bits or greater", "description": "<blockquote>\nVarious pieces of software in the OSG stack will no longer accept X.509 proxies of less than 1024 bits.  In some versions of globus that HTCondor is/was using, the default is 512 bits.  This forces HTCondor to make sure all proxies are at least 1024 bits.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2014-Jan-23 07:32:19 by bbockelm:</em> <br/>\n\nFWIW - this is not really an OSG software issue\u00a0per se, but due to the OpenSSL that ships with RHEL 6.5.\n\n<p></p><hr/>\n<em>2014-Feb-05 13:25:16 by jfrey:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>Code Review</strong>\n\n<p>This change looks ok.</p></blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-Feb-07 12:20</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/b2c56c42c62df83d50112778e8b41d8218f2af46\">[39357]</a></span>: add ticket <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=4168\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4168'); return false;\" title=\"Have HTCondor force proxies to be 1024 bits or greater\">#4168</a></span> to version history item and update defn of knob GSI_DELEGATION_KEYBITS  (By Karen Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-Feb-06 17:19</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/bd0797bd47ba3b60ae2baec7aec811f739d17697\">[39354]</a></span>: Add version history for 1024 bit delegations. <span class=\"tick